{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Overlay the MOC of Spitzer on a 2MASS cutout"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import astropy.units as u\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from astropy.io import fits\n",
    "from astropy.visualization import simple_norm\n",
    "from astropy.wcs import WCS\n",
    "from mocpy import MOC"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# load 2MASS cutout covering the galactic plane\n",
    "hdu = fits.open(\n",
    "    \"http://alasky.u-strasbg.fr/hips-image-services/hips2fits?hips=CDS%2FP%2F2MASS%2FK&width=1200&height=700&fov=30&projection=TAN&coordsys=galactic&rotation_angle=0.0&object=gal%20center&format=fits\",\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# load Spitzer MOC\n",
    "moc = MOC.from_fits(\"http://skies.esac.esa.int/Spitzer/IRAC1_bright_ISM/Moc.fits\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# create WCS from 2MASS image header\n",
    "twomass_wcs = WCS(header=hdu[0].header)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(111, figsize=(15, 10))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1, projection=twomass_wcs)\n",
    "moc.fill(ax=ax, wcs=twomass_wcs, alpha=0.3, color=\"red\")\n",
    "im = ax.imshow(\n",
    "    hdu[0].data,\n",
    "    origin=\"lower\",\n",
    "    norm=simple_norm(hdu[0].data, \"sqrt\", min_cut=0, max_cut=150),\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# compute skycoords for every pixel of the image\n",
    "width = hdu[0].header[\"NAXIS1\"]\n",
    "height = hdu[0].header[\"NAXIS2\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "xv, yv = np.meshgrid(np.arange(0, width), np.arange(0, height))\n",
    "skycoords = twomass_wcs.pixel_to_world(xv, yv)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ra, dec = skycoords.icrs.ra.deg, skycoords.icrs.dec.deg"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mask_in_moc = moc.contains_lonlat(ra * u.deg, dec * u.deg)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "img = hdu[0].data\n",
    "img_test = img.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "img_test[~mask_in_moc] = 0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(111, figsize=(15, 10))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1, projection=twomass_wcs)\n",
    "\n",
    "im = ax.imshow(\n",
    "    img_test,\n",
    "    origin=\"lower\",\n",
    "    norm=simple_norm(hdu[0].data, \"sqrt\", min_cut=0, max_cut=150),\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "8690767.0"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# number of pixels in the mask\n",
    "np.sum(img[mask_in_moc])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "14976694.0"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# number of pixels in the entire image\n",
    "np.sum(img)"
   ]
  }
 ],
